section.section:
For purposes of this subsection, "affiliation" means:
a financial interest, as defined in § 15-102 of the State Government Article;
a position of governance, including membership on a board of directors, regardless of compensation;
a relationship through which compensation, as defined in § 15-102 of the State Government Article, is received; or
a relationship for the provision of services as a regulated lobbyist, as defined in § 15-102 of the State Government Article.
